          <mj-spacer height="30px" />
          <mj-text mj-class="orange h2">Everything you need to know about HTTP security headers</mj-text>
          <mj-image src="https://blog.keycdn.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/http-security-headers.png"></mj-image>
          <mj-text>What can be attacked must be defended, and since tradition requires all security features to be a bolted-on afterthought, things… got a little complicated.</mj-text>
          <mj-text>This article explains what secure headers are and how to implement these headers in Rails, Django, Express.js, Go, Nginx, and Apache.</mj-text>
          <mj-button background-color="#F39000" href="https://blog.appcanary.com/2017/http-security-headers.html">
            Read More
          </mj-button>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>


      <!-- Additional Articles -->
      <mj-section background-color="#fff">
